\begin_layout Enumerate
The company has the choice of performing a marketing campaign for their
 product.
 The marketing campaign costs $300 and is believed to increase sales by
 
\begin_inset Formula $20\%$
\end_inset

 compared to when no campaign is performed.
 The company sells the product for 
\begin_inset Formula $p=10$
\end_inset

 dollar and the cost of producing the product is 
\begin_inset Formula $q=5$
\end_inset

 dollar.
 There are no fixed production costs.
 Assume that the company's utility is described by 
\begin_inset Formula $U(y)=1-\exp(-y/1000)$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 is the total profit from sales in the next month.
 Should the company perform the marketing campaign? [Hint: the expected
 value of the exponential function of a normal random variable 
\begin_inset Formula $S\sim N(\mu,\sigma^{2})$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $E(\exp(S))=\exp(\mu+\sigma^{2}/2)$
\end_inset

.]  
\end_layout

